y experiences) and you'll lose minimal people.  Speed is key.<br>
<br>
Also, when fighting a mob that pops Sirran, unless you wanna see dead rangers (and who doesn't?..=p) have them lay off the bow near end of fight.  Talvarien likes to send a wild arrow into Sirran like clockwork.<br>
<br>
Different methods for different people.  That's the one I use. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/leopa/misc/riverdane_animatedbanner.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seranotf>SeranoTF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/30/03 4:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4205.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tribalfury.org/images/clanmemberspict/Serano.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> heh heh.. .if it is your first DT mob - Cheer!<br>
